Document Title: 

</HEADER>

<ABS>  FBIS Report: Central Eurasia </ABS>
<DATE1>   9 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> RUSSIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decree on Aid to Khabarovsk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  944F0282B Khabarovsk TIKHOOKEANSKAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 10 
Dec 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> 944F0282B </F>
<F P=104>  Khabarovsk TIKHOOKEANSKAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Decree No. 1260 of the Council of Ministers-Government of </F>
the Russian Federation dated 4 December 1993: "On Measures for 
Stabilization of the Socioeconomic Situation of Khabarovsk Kray 
During 1993-1996"] 
  [Text] Taking into account the extreme situation that has 
developed in the economy of Khabarovsk Kray in connection with 
the liberalization of prices of energy sources and the increased 
transportation rates, and also in order to stabilize the 
socioeconomic situation of the kray, the Council of 
Ministers-Government of the Russian Federation decrees: 
  1. The Russian Federation State Committee for Socioeconomic 
Development of the North, the Russian Federation Ministry of 
Economics, and the Russian Federation Ministry of Finance in 
conjunction with the administration of Khabarovsk Kray shall 
before 1 January 1994 submit to the Council of 
Ministers-Government of the Russian Federation proposals for 
including the entire territory of Khabarovsk Kray on the list of 
localities categorized with regions of the Far North because of 
conditions for delivery and shipment of products for production 
and technical purposes as well as consumer goods. 
  2. The Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation, the 
Ministry of Economics of the Russian Federation, and the 
Ministry of Fuel and Energy of the Russian Federation, in order 
to maintain the cost of one kilowatt-hour of electric energy in 
Khabarovsk Kray at the level of R40 (calculated cost), shall 
envision the allotment to the administration of Khabarovsk Kray 
as a special-purpose selective subsidy during November-December 
1993, R19.6 billion out of the Russian Federation republic 
budget to compensate for the difference between the cost of 
electric energy produced by the Khabarovskenergo Joint-Stock 
Company and the calculated cost. 
  The administration of Khabarovsk Kray in conjunction with 
the 
Russian Federation Ministry of Fuel and Energy shall submit to 
the Council of Ministers-Government of the Russian Federation 
substantiated proposals for maintaining the calculated cost of 1 
kwh of electric energy in Khabarovsk Kray during each quarter of 
1994. 
  3. The Russian Federation Ministry of Economics, the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Finance, the Russian Federation Ministry 
of Fuel and Energy, and the Khabarovsk Kray administration shall 
envision, beginning in 1994, the financing of work for 
increasing the reliability of the energy supply for Khabarovsk 
Kray cities and introducing energy capacities in the kray 
financed by the special-purpose fund for financial support for 
energy and electrification, funds of the Russian Federation 
republic budget, and enterprises and organizations that are 
consumers of thermal and electric energy. 
  4. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finance and the 
Russian 
Federation Ministry of Fuel and Energy, in order to increase 
capacities for extracting coal from deposits in Khabarovsk Kray, 
in keeping with Russian Federation Decree No. 389 of 9 June 
1992, "On Measures for Stabilization of the Situation in the 
Fuel and Energy Complex of the Far East and Eastern Siberia 
During 1992 and the Period up to 1995," shall provide financing 
for the construction of a section of open-pit work for the 
Uralskoye Mining Administration in the volume determined by this 
decree and based on limits of capital investments for 1993 with 
subsequent allotment of funds for 1994-1996. 
  5. The Russian Federation Ministry of Fuel and Energy in 
conjunction with the Khabarovsk Kray administration shall 
develop and submit before 1 July 1994 to the Council of 
Ministers-Government of the Russian Federation a program for the 
development during the period of 1994-2000 of the coal industry 
in Khabarovsk Kray on the basis of the Urgalskoye hard coal 
basin and the Lianskoye and Khurmulinskoye brown coal deposits. 
  6. The Russian Federation Ministry of Economics, the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Finance, the Russian Federation Committee 
for Geology and the Utilization of Minerals, and the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Fuel and Energy shall provide for the 
allotment of budget funds to prospect for coal, petroleum, and 
gas in 1994 at the level of volumes allotted in 1992 (with the 
corresponding indexation). 
  7. The Russian Federation Ministry of Fuel and Energy and 
the 
Russian Federation Ministry of Economics when preparing the 
agreement on the assimilation of the Piltun-Astokhskoye and 
Lunskoye deposits of petroleum and gas on the shelf of Sakhalin 
Island, shall take into account the needs of Khabarovsk Kray 
with respect to deliveries of natural gas from petroleum and gas 
raw material of the aforementioned shelf. 
  8. The Russian Federation Ministry of Economics, the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Finance, and the Russian Federation State 
Committee for Defense Branches of Industry shall provide, in 
keeping with the established procedure, for the allotment during 
1994-1996 to defense enterprises of Khabarovsk Kray of monetary 
funds on a reimbursable basis for implementation of improved 
conversion programs and also subsidies from the state conversion 
fund used for labor compensation for workers of these 
enterprises and maintenance of the social infrastructure. 
  9. The Russian Federation Ministry of Defense and other 
Russian Federation ministries and departments which are state 
clients shall provide for presenting by the established 
deadlines to enterprises manufacturing arms and military 
equipment in Khabarovsk Kray assignments in keeping with the 
state defense order for 1994. When determining state orders for 
arms and military equipment they shall envision the maximum 
possible loading of capacities of the aforementioned enterprises. 
  10. The Russian Federation Ministry of Defense and the 
Russian Federation Ministry of Finance shall provide for 
repayment of indebtedness to enterprises that manufacture arms 
and military equipment in Khabarovsk Kray for state orders that 
have been filled. 
  11. The Russian Federation Ministry of Transportation, the 
Russian Federation Ministry of Railways, and the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Economics when formulating the Russian 
Federation state investment program for 1994 and subsequent 
years shall envision the development of the commercial seaports 
of Vanino and Sovetskaya Gavan and the reconstruction of the 
railroad line Komsomolsk-na-Amur to Vanino as a part of the 
program entitled "Regeneration of the Commercial Fleet of Russia 
During 1993-2000." 
  12. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finance when 
determining relations between the Russian Federation republic 
budget and the Khabarovsk Kray budget for 1994 shall take into 
account expenditures necessary for: 
  --completion of construction and startup of the Baykal-Amur 
Poultry Factory in the city of Komsomolsk-na-Amur; 
  --the acquisition of urban passenger transportation; 
  --land reclamation work. 
  13. The Russian Federation Ministry of Economics and the 
Roskhleboprodukt Joint-Stock Company, beginning in 1994, shall 
envision deliveries of grain to Khabarovsk Kray from the federal 
fund through the Eksportkhleb Joint-Stock Company through ports 
of the Far East. 
  14. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finance when 
formulating the budget system for 1994-1996 shall take into 
account in the Khabarovsk Kray budget expenditures on financing 
incomplete construction of facilities for municipal services 
transferred to municipal ownership by enterprises and 
departments located on the territory of the kray. 
  15. The Russian Federation Ministry of Economics and the 
Russian Federation Ministry of Finance in conjunction with 
interested Russian Federation ministries and departments and the 
Khabarovsk Kray administration shall within a month's time 
develop and submit to the Council of Ministers-Government of the 
Russian Federation proposals for special-purpose use beginning 
in 1994 of allocations for the development of the foreign 
economic infrastructure of the kray in an amount of up to 20 
percent of the funds transferred into the Russian Federation 
republic budget from collections by customs control organs of 
customs duties on Khabarovsk Kray territory. 
  [Signed] Chairman of the Council of Ministers-Government of 
the Russian Federation V. Chernomyrdin 

</TEXT>

