<H3> <TI>   Magadan Gold Mining Figures Cited </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  944F0277A Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 18 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0277A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the rubric "ADS reports": </F>
"Magadan Oblast Revises Gold Production Data"] 
  [Text] Preliminary results of gold production in Magadan 
Oblast, according to which gold output in 1993 fell by 4 tonnes 
(-8 percent) compared to 1992 (see SEGODNYA No. 85), were not 
confirmed. According to revised but still not final data which 
was released by the Northeastern Geological Committee, last year 
the oblast turned over to the state 28,561 tonnes of gold 
(29,156 tonnes in 1992). During the 11 months the 
Severovostokzoloto produced 22,502 tonnes (25,262 tonnes in all 
of 1992). Gold mining cooperatives and new gold-producing 
structures which do not belong to the Severovostokzoloto 
produced 4,773 tonnes (3,894 tonnes). According to Vladimir 
Banin, deputy head of the Magadan Oblast Administration, there 
are grounds to believe that not all of the metal produced last 
year has been turned over to the state yet. 

</TEXT>

