<ABS>  FBIS Report: Central Eurasia </ABS>
<DATE1>   9 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> RUSSIA </F>
<F P=101> POLITICAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statute on Russian Federation State Service Approved </TI></H3>
<H4>   Edict Approving Statute </H4>
<F P=102> 944F0261A Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 5 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0261A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> ["Edict of the President of the Russian Federation: On the </F>
Federal State Service"] 
  [Text] For purposes of providing for the function of the 
Federal State Service I decree 
  1. The Statute on the Federal State Service (appended) shall 
be approved. 
  2. It shall be established that, from the moment the present 
Edict goes into effect, all individuals holding state positions 
in the Administration of the President of the Russian 
Federation, the apparatus of the Government of the Russian 
Federation, the apparatus of the Security Council of the Russian 
Federation, the apparatuses of the chambers of the Federal 
Assembly of the Russian Federation, the Constitutional Court of 
the Russian Federation, the Supreme Court of the Russian 
Federation, the High Arbitration Court of the Russian 
Federation, and in federal organs of state power shall be 
considered to be in the Federal State Service. Work in staff 
positions in other federal state organizations and institutions 
shall be included in the Federal State Service by decisions of 
the president of the Russian Federation at the suggestion of the 
Personnel Policy Council under the President of the Russian 
Federation. 
  3. The statute on the Federal State Service shall not apply 
to individuals for whom questions of working in the state 
service and holding state positions are regulated by laws of the 
Russian Federation adopted before the present Edict takes effect. 
  The present statute shall not regulate issues of positions 
of 
members of the Government of the Russian Federation, the head of 
the Administration of the President of the Russian Federation, 
and the secretary of the Security Council of the Russian 
Federation and also positions filled by appointment in order to 
provide for the political activity of individuals holding the 
aforementioned positions. In the future up until the adoption of 
a special legislative act regulating questions of the 
aforementioned positions, social guarantees established by the 
Statute on Federal State Service shall apply to individuals 
holding these positions in organs of executive power specified 
by the Constitution of the Russian Federation. 
  4. Regulations on discipline established previously in state 
organs by legislation of the Russian Federation and also ranks 
and titles for particular kinds of state service shall be 
retained. 
  5. The Government of the Russian Federation shall develop 
and 
submit drafts of acts of the president of the Russian 
Federation, the need for whose adoption ensues from the Statute 
on Federal State Service, and also on the basis of an analysis 
of the application of the aforementioned Statute--a draft law of 
the Russian Federation on the Federal State Service. 
  6. The present Edict shall be presented for the 
consideration 
of the Federal Assembly of the Russian Federation. 
  7. The present Edict shall take effect the day of its 
publication. 
  [Signed] President of the Russian Federation B. Yeltsin 
  Moscow, The Kremlin 
  22 December 1993 
  No. 2267 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

