<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Pay What Has Been Earned! Third Call"] </F>
  [Text] Moscow--Disturbing news: The oil workers of the 
Republic of Komi are once again threatening to shut off the 
valves. They really do have more than enough reason to strike: 
wages in Usinsk, Ukhta, and the majority of other 
administrations of the Komineft Stock Company have not been paid 
since last November. 
  Today the situation is exacerbated in the extreme: the 
Presidium of the Russian Council of the Union of Workers of the 
Oil and Gas Sectors of Industry and Construction 
(Neftegazstroyprofsoyuz) has sent an appeal to all oil-producing 
associations for support for the "ultimatum" of the oil workers 
of Usinsk. It is demanded that the Governments of the Russian 
Federation and Komi make good the wage arrears before 1 February 
and settle accounts in full for the oil that has been supplied 
to the consumers. 
  As Valeriy Bendyuzhik, deputy chairman of the Komi Republic 
Neftegazstroyprofsoyuz Committee, announced, in the event of 
this warning going unheeded by the authorities, the union will 
be forced to adopt, in accordance with the law, a decision on 
the date of commencement of a strike. 

</TEXT>

